\f1\b0\fs46 \cf0 Marinade: Put the pork in a roasting pan. Combine all the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/marinade/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 marinade}} ingredients in a small bowl. Pour the marinade over the pork and massage it into the meat. Cover and refrigerate ovemight.\
Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.\
After marinating, put the covered roasting pan in the oven and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/roast/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 roast}} for 1 hour while preparing the salsa.\
Cook's Note: You will prepare the roasted peppers, Italian dressing, and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/salsa/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 salsa}} base separately, and then combine them together in the end of the recipe before simmering together with the pork.\
Salsa:\
Put the water and tomatoes, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/onion/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 onions}}, garlic, bell pepper, and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/celery/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 celery}} in large pot over medium heat and bring to a boil. Cook for 15 minutes.\
Roasted peppers:\
Over an open flame, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/grill/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 grill}}, or {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/griddle/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 griddle}} over high heat, roast all the peppers, approximately 2 minutes. Add the sesame seeds to a small skillet over low heat and toast. Set aside.\
Italian dressing:\
Vigorously mix all the ingredients in a small bowl and set aside.\
Add the roasted peppers, sesame seeds and boiled vegetables to a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/blender/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 blender}} along with the Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce, oregano, granulated garlic, bread and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cilantro/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cilantro}} leaves. Blend until smooth.\
Add the Italian dressing and blend thoroughly.\
Put the mixture into large {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/saucepan/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 saucepan}} over medium heat and bring to boil. Lower the heat and simmer for 10 minutes.\
Remove the pork from the oven to a cutting board and cut into bite-size chunks.\
Add the pork pieces to the saucepan over medium heat and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/simmer/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 simmer}} for 25 minutes. Transfer to a serving bowl and serve.\
